  "root_text": {
    "snp1.7:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 1.7 ",
    "snp1.7:0.2": "Vasalasutta ",
    "snp1.7:1.1": "Evaṁ me sutaṁ—",
    "snp1.7:1.2": "ekaṁ samayaṁ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṁ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. ",
    "snp1.7:1.3": "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṁ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṁ piṇḍāya pāvisi. ",
    "snp1.7:1.4": "Tena kho pana samayena aggikabhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa nivesane aggi pajjalito hoti āhuti paggahitā. ",
    "snp1.7:1.5": "Atha kho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṁ sapadānaṁ piṇḍāya caramāno yena aggikabhāradvājassa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṁ tenupasaṅkami. ",
    "snp1.7:2.1": "Addasā kho aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṁ dūratova āgacchantaṁ. ",
    "snp1.7:2.2": "Disvāna bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "snp1.7:2.3": "“tatreva, muṇḍaka; ",
    "snp1.7:2.4": "tatreva, samaṇaka; ",
    "snp1.7:2.5": "tatreva, vasalaka, tiṭṭhāhī”ti. ",
    "snp1.7:3.1": "Evaṁ vutte, bhagavā aggikabhāradvājaṁ brāhmaṇaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "snp1.7:3.2": "“jānāsi pana tvaṁ, brāhmaṇa, vasalaṁ vā vasalakaraṇe vā dhamme”ti? ",
    "snp1.7:3.3": "“Na khvāhaṁ, bho gotama, jānāmi vasalaṁ vā vasalakaraṇe vā dhamme; ",
    "snp1.7:3.4": "sādhu me bhavaṁ gotamo tathā dhammaṁ desetu, yathāhaṁ jāneyyaṁ vasalaṁ vā vasalakaraṇe vā dhamme”ti. ",
    "snp1.7:3.5": "“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, suṇāhi, sādhukaṁ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. ",
    "snp1.7:3.6": "“Evaṁ, bho”ti kho aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavato paccassosi. ",
    "snp1.7:3.7": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
    "snp1.7:4.1": "“Kodhano upanāhī ca, ",
    "snp1.7:4.2": "pāpamakkhī ca yo naro; ",
    "snp1.7:4.3": "Vipannadiṭṭhi māyāvī, ",
    "snp1.7:4.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:5.1": "Ekajaṁ vā dvijaṁ vāpi, ",
    "snp1.7:5.2": "yodha pāṇaṁ vihiṁsati; ",
    "snp1.7:5.3": "Yassa pāṇe dayā natthi, ",
    "snp1.7:5.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:6.1": "Yo hanti parirundhati, ",
    "snp1.7:6.2": "gāmāni nigamāni ca; ",
    "snp1.7:6.3": "Niggāhako samaññāto, ",
    "snp1.7:6.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:7.1": "Gāme vā yadi vā raññe, ",
    "snp1.7:7.2": "yaṁ paresaṁ mamāyitaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:7.3": "Theyyā adinnamādeti, ",
    "snp1.7:7.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:8.1": "Yo have iṇamādāya, ",
    "snp1.7:8.2": "cujjamāno palāyati; ",
    "snp1.7:8.3": "Na hi te iṇamatthīti, ",
    "snp1.7:8.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:9.1": "Yo ve kiñcikkhakamyatā, ",
    "snp1.7:9.2": "panthasmiṁ vajantaṁ janaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:9.3": "Hantvā kiñcikkhamādeti, ",
    "snp1.7:9.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:10.1": "Attahetu parahetu, ",
    "snp1.7:10.2": "dhanahetu ca yo naro; ",
    "snp1.7:10.3": "Sakkhipuṭṭho musā brūti, ",
    "snp1.7:10.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:11.1": "Yo ñātīnaṁ sakhīnaṁ vā, ",
    "snp1.7:11.2": "dāresu paṭidissati; ",
    "snp1.7:11.3": "Sāhasā sampiyena vā, ",
    "snp1.7:11.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:12.1": "Yo mātaraṁ pitaraṁ vā, ",
    "snp1.7:12.2": "jiṇṇakaṁ gatayobbanaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:12.3": "Pahu santo na bharati, ",
    "snp1.7:12.4": "taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:13.1": "Yo mātaraṁ pitaraṁ vā, ",
    "snp1.7:13.2": "Bhātaraṁ bhaginiṁ sasuṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:13.3": "Hanti roseti vācāya, ",
    "snp1.7:13.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:14.1": "Yo atthaṁ pucchito santo, ",
    "snp1.7:14.2": "Anatthamanusāsati; ",
    "snp1.7:14.3": "Paṭicchannena manteti, ",
    "snp1.7:14.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:15.1": "Yo katvā pāpakaṁ kammaṁ, ",
    "snp1.7:15.2": "Mā maṁ jaññāti icchati; ",
    "snp1.7:15.3": "Yo paṭicchannakammanto, ",
    "snp1.7:15.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:16.1": "Yo ve parakulaṁ gantvā, ",
    "snp1.7:16.2": "Bhutvāna sucibhojanaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:16.3": "Āgataṁ nappaṭipūjeti, ",
    "snp1.7:16.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:17.1": "Yo brāhmaṇaṁ samaṇaṁ vā, ",
    "snp1.7:17.2": "Aññaṁ vāpi vanibbakaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:17.3": "Musāvādena vañceti, ",
    "snp1.7:17.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:18.1": "Yo brāhmaṇaṁ samaṇaṁ vā, ",
    "snp1.7:18.2": "Bhattakāle upaṭṭhite; ",
    "snp1.7:18.3": "Roseti vācā na ca deti, ",
    "snp1.7:18.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:19.1": "Asataṁ yodha pabrūti, ",
    "snp1.7:19.2": "Mohena paliguṇṭhito; ",
    "snp1.7:19.3": "Kiñcikkhaṁ nijigīsāno, ",
    "snp1.7:19.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:20.1": "Yo cattānaṁ samukkaṁse, ",
    "snp1.7:20.2": "Pare ca mavajānāti; ",
    "snp1.7:20.3": "Nihīno sena mānena, ",
    "snp1.7:20.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:21.1": "Rosako kadariyo ca, ",
    "snp1.7:21.2": "Pāpiccho maccharī saṭho; ",
    "snp1.7:21.3": "Ahiriko anottappī, ",
    "snp1.7:21.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:22.1": "Yo buddhaṁ paribhāsati, ",
    "snp1.7:22.2": "Atha vā tassa sāvakaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:22.3": "Paribbājaṁ gahaṭṭhaṁ vā, ",
    "snp1.7:22.4": "Taṁ jaññā vasalo iti. ",
    "snp1.7:23.1": "Yo ve anarahaṁ santo, ",
    "snp1.7:23.2": "Arahaṁ paṭijānāti; ",
    "snp1.7:23.3": "Coro sabrahmake loke, ",
    "snp1.7:23.4": "Eso kho vasalādhamo; ",
    "snp1.7:23.5": "Ete kho vasalā vuttā, ",
    "snp1.7:23.6": "Mayā yete pakāsitā. ",
    "snp1.7:24.1": "Na jaccā vasalo hoti, ",
    "snp1.7:24.2": "Na jaccā hoti brāhmaṇo; ",
    "snp1.7:24.3": "Kammunā vasalo hoti, ",
    "snp1.7:24.4": "Kammunā hoti brāhmaṇo. ",
    "snp1.7:25.1": "Tadamināpi jānātha, ",
    "snp1.7:25.2": "Yathāmedaṁ nidassanaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:25.3": "Caṇḍālaputto sopāko, ",
    "snp1.7:25.4": "Mātaṅgo iti vissuto. ",
    "snp1.7:26.1": "So yasaṁ paramaṁ patto, ",
    "snp1.7:26.2": "Mātaṅgo yaṁ sudullabhaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:26.3": "Āgacchuṁ tassupaṭṭhānaṁ, ",
    "snp1.7:26.4": "Khattiyā brāhmaṇā bahū. ",
    "snp1.7:27.1": "Devayānaṁ abhiruyha, ",
    "snp1.7:27.2": "Virajaṁ so mahāpathaṁ; ",
    "snp1.7:27.3": "Kāmarāgaṁ virājetvā, ",
    "snp1.7:27.4": "Brahmalokūpago ahu; ",
    "snp1.7:27.5": "Na naṁ jāti nivāresi, ",
    "snp1.7:27.6": "Brahmalokūpapattiyā. ",
    "snp1.7:28.1": "Ajjhāyakakule jātā, ",
    "snp1.7:28.2": "Brāhmaṇā mantabandhavā; ",
    "snp1.7:28.3": "Te ca pāpesu kammesu, ",
    "snp1.7:28.4": "Abhiṇhamupadissare. ",
    "snp1.7:29.1": "Diṭṭheva dhamme gārayhā, ",
    "snp1.7:29.2": "Samparāye ca duggati; ",
    "snp1.7:29.3": "Na ne jāti nivāreti, ",
    "snp1.7:29.4": "Duggatyā garahāya vā. ",
    "snp1.7:30.1": "Na jaccā vasalo hoti, ",
    "snp1.7:30.2": "Na jaccā hoti brāhmaṇo; ",
    "snp1.7:30.3": "Kammunā vasalo hoti, ",
    "snp1.7:30.4": "Kammunā hoti brāhmaṇo”ti. ",
    "snp1.7:31.1": "Evaṁ vutte, aggikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṁ etadavoca: ",
    "snp1.7:31.2": "“abhikkantaṁ, bho gotama …pe… ",
    "snp1.7:31.3": "upāsakaṁ maṁ bhavaṁ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṁ saraṇaṁ gatan”ti. ",
    "snp1.7:31.4": "Vasalasuttaṁ sattamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp1.7:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 1.7 ",
    "snp1.7:0.2": "The Lowlife ",
    "snp1.7:1.1": "So I have heard. ",
    "snp1.7:1.2": "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. ",
    "snp1.7:1.3": "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, entered Sāvatthī for alms. ",
    "snp1.7:1.4": "Now at that time in the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper’s home the sacred flame had been kindled and the oblation prepared. ",
    "snp1.7:1.5": "Wandering indiscriminately for almsfood in Sāvatthī, the Buddha approached Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper’s house. ",
    "snp1.7:2.1": "Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper saw the Buddha coming off in the distance ",
    "snp1.7:2.2": "and said to him, ",
    "snp1.7:2.3": "“Stop right there, shaveling! ",
    "snp1.7:2.4": "Right there, fake ascetic! ",
    "snp1.7:2.5": "Right there, lowlife!” ",
    "snp1.7:3.1": "When he said this, the Buddha said to him, ",
    "snp1.7:3.2": "“But brahmin, do you know what is a lowlife or what are the qualities that make you a lowlife?” ",
    "snp1.7:3.3": "“No I do not, worthy Gotama. ",
    "snp1.7:3.4": "Please, worthy Gotama, teach me this matter so I can understand what is a lowlife or what are the qualities that make you a lowlife.” ",
    "snp1.7:3.5": "“Well then, brahmin, listen and apply your mind well, I will speak.” ",
    "snp1.7:3.6": "“Yes, worthy sir,” Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper replied. ",
    "snp1.7:3.7": "The Buddha said this: ",
    "snp1.7:4.1": "“Irritable and acrimonious, ",
    "snp1.7:4.2": "wicked and offensive, ",
    "snp1.7:4.3": "a man deficient in view, deceitful: ",
    "snp1.7:4.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:5.1": "He harms living creatures ",
    "snp1.7:5.2": "born of womb or of egg, ",
    "snp1.7:5.3": "and has no kindness for creatures: ",
    "snp1.7:5.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:6.1": "He destroys and devastates ",
    "snp1.7:6.2": "villages and towns, ",
    "snp1.7:6.3": "a notorious oppressor: ",
    "snp1.7:6.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:7.1": "Whether in village or wilderness, ",
    "snp1.7:7.2": "he steals what belongs to others, ",
    "snp1.7:7.3": "taking what has not been given: ",
    "snp1.7:7.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:8.1": "Having fallen into debt, ",
    "snp1.7:8.2": "when pressed to pay up he flees, saying ",
    "snp1.7:8.3": "‘I don’t owe you anything!’: ",
    "snp1.7:8.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:9.1": "Wanting some item or other, ",
    "snp1.7:9.2": "he attacks a person in the street ",
    "snp1.7:9.3": "and takes it: ",
    "snp1.7:9.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:10.1": "For his own sake or the sake of another, ",
    "snp1.7:10.2": "or for the sake of wealth, a man ",
    "snp1.7:10.3": "tells a lie when asked to bear witness: ",
    "snp1.7:10.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:11.1": "He is spied among the partners ",
    "snp1.7:11.2": "of relatives and friends, ",
    "snp1.7:11.3": "by force or seduction: ",
    "snp1.7:11.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:12.1": "Though able, he does not look after ",
    "snp1.7:12.2": "his mother and father ",
    "snp1.7:12.3": "when elderly, past their prime: ",
    "snp1.7:12.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:13.1": "He hits or verbally abuses ",
    "snp1.7:13.2": "his mother or father, ",
    "snp1.7:13.3": "brother, sister, or mother-in-law: ",
    "snp1.7:13.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:14.1": "When asked about the good, ",
    "snp1.7:14.2": "he teaches what is bad, ",
    "snp1.7:14.3": "giving secretive advice: ",
    "snp1.7:14.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:15.1": "Having done a bad deed, he wishes, ",
    "snp1.7:15.2": "‘May no-one find me out!’ ",
    "snp1.7:15.3": "His deeds are underhand: ",
    "snp1.7:15.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:16.1": "When visiting another family ",
    "snp1.7:16.2": "he eats their delicious food, ",
    "snp1.7:16.3": "but does not return the honor: ",
    "snp1.7:16.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:17.1": "He deceives with lies ",
    "snp1.7:17.2": "ascetics and brahmins ",
    "snp1.7:17.3": "and other supplicants: ",
    "snp1.7:17.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:18.1": "When time comes to offer a meal ",
    "snp1.7:18.2": "to brahmins or ascetics, ",
    "snp1.7:18.3": "he abuses them and does not give: ",
    "snp1.7:18.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:19.1": "He talks about what never happened, ",
    "snp1.7:19.2": "being wrapped up in delusion, ",
    "snp1.7:19.3": "chasing after some item or other: ",
    "snp1.7:19.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:20.1": "He extols himself ",
    "snp1.7:20.2": "and disparages others, ",
    "snp1.7:20.3": "brought down by his pride: ",
    "snp1.7:20.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:21.1": "He’s a bully and a miser, ",
    "snp1.7:21.2": "of corrupt wishes, stingy, and devious, ",
    "snp1.7:21.3": "shameless, imprudent: ",
    "snp1.7:21.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:22.1": "He insults the Buddha ",
    "snp1.7:22.2": "or his disciple, ",
    "snp1.7:22.3": "whether lay or renunciate: ",
    "snp1.7:22.4": "know him as a lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:23.1": "He claims to be a perfected one, ",
    "snp1.7:23.2": "when he really is no such thing. ",
    "snp1.7:23.3": "In the world with its divinities, ",
    "snp1.7:23.4": "that crook is truly the lowest lowlife. ",
    "snp1.7:23.5": "These who are called lowlifes ",
    "snp1.7:23.6": "I have explained to you. ",
    "snp1.7:24.1": "You’re not a lowlife by birth, ",
    "snp1.7:24.2": "nor by birth are you a brahmin. ",
    "snp1.7:24.3": "You’re a lowlife by your deeds, ",
    "snp1.7:24.4": "by deeds you’re a brahmin. ",
    "snp1.7:25.1": "And also you should know ",
    "snp1.7:25.2": "according to this example. ",
    "snp1.7:25.3": "A corpse-worker’s son of the dog-eating caste ",
    "snp1.7:25.4": "became renowned as Mātaṅga. ",
    "snp1.7:26.1": "Mātaṅga achieved the highest fame ",
    "snp1.7:26.2": "so very hard to find. ",
    "snp1.7:26.3": "Lots of aristocrats and brahmins ",
    "snp1.7:26.4": "came to serve him. ",
    "snp1.7:27.1": "He ascended the stainless highway ",
    "snp1.7:27.2": "that leads to the heavens; ",
    "snp1.7:27.3": "having discarded sensual desire, ",
    "snp1.7:27.4": "he was reborn in a realm of divinity. ",
    "snp1.7:27.5": "His birth did not prevent him ",
    "snp1.7:27.6": "from rebirth in the realm of divinity. ",
    "snp1.7:28.1": "Those born in a brahmin family ",
    "snp1.7:28.2": "who recite as kinsmen of the hymns, ",
    "snp1.7:28.3": "are often discovered ",
    "snp1.7:28.4": "in the midst of wicked deeds. ",
    "snp1.7:29.1": "Blameworthy in this very life, ",
    "snp1.7:29.2": "and in the next, a bad destination. ",
    "snp1.7:29.3": "Their birth does not prevent them ",
    "snp1.7:29.4": "from blame or bad destiny. ",
    "snp1.7:30.1": "You’re not a lowlife by birth, ",
    "snp1.7:30.2": "nor by birth are you a brahmin. ",
    "snp1.7:30.3": "You’re a lowlife by your deeds, ",
    "snp1.7:30.4": "by deeds you’re a brahmin.” ",
    "snp1.7:31.1": "When he had spoken, the brahmin Bhāradvāja the Fire-Worshiper said to the Buddha, ",
    "snp1.7:31.2": "“Excellent, worthy Gotama! Excellent! … ",
    "snp1.7:31.3": "From this day forth, may the worthy Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "
  },
